# Crescia — Cursor AI Rules
# AP/IB/SAT Exam Prep Platform with Garden Gamification
# Stack: Next.js 14 · TypeScript · Tailwind CSS · shadcn/ui · Supabase · Clerk · Stripe · Anthropic API

## PROJECT IDENTITY
- Product name: Crescia
- Purpose: Gamified AP/IB/SAT exam prep platform with a garden-growth mechanic
- MVP subjects: AP Statistics, AP Biology, AP Calculus AB/BC
- Primary users: High school students (16–18), secondary: parents

## ARCHITECTURE RULES
- Framework: Next.js 14 with App Router. Never use Pages Router.
- All pages live under /app. All API logic lives in /app/api or as Server Actions.
- NEVER call the Anthropic API from the browser or client components. All AI calls go through Server Actions or API Routes only.
- NEVER expose API keys client-side. All secrets live in .env.local and are accessed server-side only.
- Use TypeScript strictly. Define interfaces for all data shapes in /types.
- Use Supabase for all database operations. Never use localStorage or sessionStorage for user data.
- Use Clerk for all authentication. Never roll custom auth.
- Row Level Security (RLS) must be enabled on every Supabase table. Always enforce user_id = auth.uid() policies.

