## CODING STANDARDS
- Use Server Actions for all data mutations (form submissions, session saves, XP updates).
- Use server components by default. Only add "use client" when strictly necessary (interactivity, hooks).
- All Supabase queries must be typed using the generated Database type from /types/supabase.ts.
- Use shadcn/ui components as the base. Customize via Tailwind only — no inline styles.
- Framer Motion is allowed for animations (XP gain, level-up, plant growth transitions only).
- Recharts is the only charting library. Use it for the readiness score history and topic heatmap.
- Never use any other UI or charting library without explicit instruction.

## AI / ANTHROPIC RULES
- Model: claude-sonnet-4-20250514 always. Never hardcode a different model.
- Always implement prompt caching for system prompts using cache_control: { type: "ephemeral" }.
- Question generation must return structured JSON. Always validate the JSON shape before saving.
- FRQ grading must return: { score: number, max_score: number, feedback: string[], rubric_points: RubricPoint[] }
- Cap AI calls with a rate limiter: free tier max 10 AI calls/day, paid tier unlimited.
- Cache generated questions in the questions_cache table before returning to client.

## DATABASE RULES
- Every table must have: id (uuid), user_id (uuid, FK to users), created_at (timestamp).
- Never delete records. Use soft deletes with a deleted_at column.
- Aggregate stats (topic accuracy, readiness score) are stored in topic_stats, not recomputed live.
- Garden state is stored in garden_plots and plants tables, not in component state.

## GAMIFICATION RULES
- XP is only awarded for correct answers. Never award XP for participation or time spent.
- Streak logic: study at least once per day = streak maintained. Grace day: 1 per week.
- Readiness score: weighted average of recent topic_stats accuracy, updated after every session.
- Plant growth: driven by streak maintenance and challenge completion, not by XP directly.
- Shards (currency): earned by correct answers, challenges, streaks. Never purchasable with money.

## PAYMENTS (STRIPE)
- Stripe is wired in TEST MODE only for MVP. Never switch to live mode without explicit instruction.
- Paywall logic must be enforced server-side in Server Actions, not just hidden in the UI.
- Free tier: 10 questions/day, 1 hint token/day, basic readiness score.
- Paid tier (Student): unlimited questions, 3 hint tokens/day, full heatmap, FRQ grader.
- Always check user plan in /lib/stripe/plan.ts before allowing gated features.

