## COMPONENT CREATION RULES
- Before creating any new component, check if shadcn/ui has one that fits.
- Every new component must have TypeScript props interface defined above the component.
- Client components must have "use client" as the very first line.
- Never put data fetching inside client components. Fetch in server components and pass as props.

## ERROR HANDLING
- All Server Actions must return { success: boolean, data?: T, error?: string }.
- All API routes must return proper HTTP status codes.
- Never expose raw error messages to the client. Log server-side, return safe messages client-side.
- Wrap all Anthropic API calls in try/catch with a fallback error message.

## NAMING CONVENTIONS
- Files: kebab-case (question-card.tsx, topic-heatmap.tsx)
- Components: PascalCase (QuestionCard, TopicHeatmap)
- Functions: camelCase (generateQuestion, updateTopicStats)
- Database tables: snake_case (topic_stats, garden_plots)
- Environment variables: SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE (ANTHROPIC_API_KEY)
- Types/Interfaces: PascalCase with descriptive names (QuestionResult, SessionSummary)

## WHEN GENERATING CODE
1. Always check the folder structure above before creating new files.
2. Always use existing types from /types before defining new ones.
3. Always use the Supabase client from /lib/supabase — never instantiate a new one.
4. Always use the Anthropic client from /lib/ai/client.ts — never instantiate a new one.
5. When in doubt about a UI component, check shadcn/ui first.
6. State what you're building, which files you're touching, and why before writing code.
